{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos944.erdos_944 https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos944.erdos_944.","id":"vf_2b4c2e3f1a80cdfe","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #944: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. A critical vertex, edge, or set of edges, is one whose deletion lowers the chromatic number.\n\nLet $k\\geq 4$ and $r\\geq 1$. Must there exist a graph $G$ with chromatic number $k$ such that every vertex is critical, yet every critical set of edges has size $>r$? Current best: This was conjectured by Dirac in 1970 for $k\\geq 4$ and $r=1$. Independently, Jensen \\cite{Je02} gave an alternative construction for all $k\\geq 5$. Martinsson and Steiner \\cite{MaSt25} proved this is true for every $r\\geq 1$ if $k$ is sufficiently large, depending on $r$. Skottova and Steiner \\cite{SkSt25} have improved this, proving that such graphs exist for all $k\\geq 5$ and $r\\geq 1$. Prize: no. Tags: chromatic number, graph theory.","id":"vf_98bf1739096e5752","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/944.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_2b4c2e3f1a80cdfe","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:944","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_2b4c2e3f1a80cdfe","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"vf_98bf1739096e5752","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes"